place.name: TUTTINGTON
place.gazetteerText: TUTTINGTON, a parish in Aylsham district, Norfolk; 4 miles SW of North Walsham r. station. Post town, Hevingham, under Norwich. Acres, 830. Real property, £1,289. Pop., 202. Houses, 47. The property is much subdivided. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £124. Patron, the Bishop of N. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
